# Project forms

## Show a project's form

Returns the form for the given `project_id`.

```shell
curl "https://screendoor.dobt.co/api/projects/2/form?v=0&api_key=d9763djh1274"

# Example Response
<%= partial 'resources/form.json' %>
```

### HTTP Request

`GET /projects/:project_id/form`

## Update a project's form

Updates the project's form.

```shell
curl "https://screendoor.dobt.co/api/projects/2/form?v=0&api_key=d9763djh1274" \
  -X PUT \
  -d field_data='[
{
  "id": "ak01k23k",
  "type": "field",
  "field_type": "text",
  "label": "Your Strategy"
}
]'

# Example Response
<%= partial 'resources/form.json' %>
```

### HTTP Request

`PUT /projects/:project_id/form`

### Options

| Parameter | Type | Default | Description |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| field_data | JSON-encoded Hash | | Sorry, the form schema is not yet documented. |

## Add a field to the form

Adds a single field to the project's form. You can manually specify an `id` in the `field_data` hash, or you can leave it blank to have one created for you.

```shell
curl "https://screendoor.dobt.co/api/projects/2/form/fields?v=0&api_key=d9763djh1274" \
  -X POST \
  -d position=0 \
  -d field_data='
{
  "type": "field",
  "field_type": "text",
  "label": "Your Strategy"
}'

# Example Response
<%= partial 'resources/form.json' %>
```

### HTTP Request

`POST /projects/:project_id/form/fields`

### Options

| Parameter | Type | Default | Description |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| field_data | JSON-encoded Hash | | Sorry, the form schema is not yet documented. |
| position | Integer | | The zero-indexed position where this field should be inserted in the form. By default, it will be inserted as the last field in the form. |

## Update a field in the form

Updates a single field in the project's form.

```shell
curl "https://screendoor.dobt.co/api/projects/2/form/fields/ak01k23k?v=0&api_key=d9763djh1274" \
  -X PUT \
  -d field_data='
{
  "type": "field",
